BT 1 0 0 1 0 87 Tm 12 TL /F1 9 Tf 0 0 0 rg (Zipf's Law \(1935\): in natural language, the frequency of any word is inversely proportional to its rank. The most common) Tj T* (word appears roughly twice as often as the second most common, three times as often as the third, etc. The distribution) Tj T* (follows f\(r\) ~ 1/r^alpha with alpha ~= 1. The same power law appears in city populations, earthquake magnitudes) Tj T* (\(Gutenberg-Richter\), neural avalanche sizes \(Beggs & Plenz 2003\), gene expression levels, species abundance, internet) Tj T* (traffic, and solar flare intensity. Power laws are not coincidence. They are the signature of systems operating at criticality --) Tj T* (at gamma_c. This paper makes explicit the connection between the Wike Coherence Law, the universality of power laws,) Tj T* (and the observation that language, brains, ecosystems, and geological systems all independently found the edge. Every) Tj T* (power law is evidence of a system at gamma_c. Every Zipf distribution is a coherence signature.) Tj T* ET
